        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pinion shims are available in the following thickness:</para>
            <table id="t1400403">
                <title>Pinion Shim Availability</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="sqcolumn1" colwidth="1in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="sqcolumn2" colwidth="1in" colsep="1"/>
                    <thead valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>IN.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>MM</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.005</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.127</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.010</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.254</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>.030</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.762</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If exact shim measurement cannot be achieved, use available shims to approximate correct
                        pinion position.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position shims on carrier housing so oil return holes align properly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f14004c3">Figure 123</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f14004c3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g14004c3" filename="../figg14/G14004C3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 122. Position Shims on Carrier Housing</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Be certain mounting surfaces and shims are free of dirt and nicks or leaks may occur and
                        pinion position can be affected.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install pinion and pinion cage assembly into carrier (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f14004c4">Figure 124</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f14004c4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g14004c4" filename="../figg14/G14004C4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 123. Install Pinion and Pinion Cage Assembly into Carrier</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Studs can be used to assist in alignment.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten pinion cage to carrier bolts to 115 to 135 ft-lbs. (156 to 183 Nm) on all forward
                carriers and the J Model rear carriers. The W Model rear carriers require 160 to 185 ft-lbs. (217 to 251
                Nm) torque (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f14004c5">Figure 125</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f14004c5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g14004c5" filename="../figg14/G14004C5.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 124. Tighten Pinion Cage to Carrier Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">An alternative to using the pinion setting gauges is to follow the procedure described under
                <hotlnk document="s14004_HL1400404.xml" xrefid="hl1400404">PINION SETTING CHART</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
